^B@2^*BHoward: ^*N|cp||at|Let me discuss the 2N by Anna. I am not going to explain whether it is or it is not a correct bid for her hand. As you may know there are several treatments for responding to reverse bids. In most 2N is used to get more information from the Reverse bidder. They are not universal, they are complicated, and hard to remember for most bridge players. Here, let me briefly discuss my method of responding once opener reverses.|
