Lebensohl, Traditional, Ingberman, and Modified Ingberman approaches are to name a few. Allegedly, they are all devised so responder with a minimum or a medium hand can use in getting additional information from the reverse bidder. In all responder bids 2N or the cheaper of the 4th suit and 2N with a minimum hand and another suit with a medium hand. To add to the confusion, responder and reverse bidder should remember which bid by responder is forcing and which one is not. And if it is forcing, is it forcing to game or not. We wonder how an average bridge partnership can remember all those fine points.|
