ht|h|aT|^B@2Ingberman convention is useful when the partner reverses and the responder is holding minimum values of 6/7 HCP which from responder's perspective is insufficient to guarantee game as reverse bidder may have minimum values–15/16 HCP. Therefore, responder must communicate this information to his partner to partnership to stop below game after opener's 2-level reverse bid. The Ingberman convention is similar to Lebensohl in bidding 2N (relay to 3@C). However, in this convention, other bids are also defined so that it is more than Lebensohl after a reverse bid. First let us let us address the SAYC vs 2/1 issue and reverse bids such as the auction below left:|
PG| ***** 226 ***** |


HT|n|cs|6|at|^B{|ia|o1h2c2s?|at|}|HT|n|at|^K@2The initial 2@C by responder in SAYC promises 10+ HCP ( top of a medium range hand for responder) and at least game is assured. The responder's rebid is standard. The only issue which should be considered when partnership plays 2/1 is whether the reverse shows extra value or not. Otherwise, partnership at least is committed to game.|
PG| ***** 227 ***** |


